==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Capper
<hw>Cap"per</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One whose
business is to make or sell caps.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A by-bidder; a decoy for gamblers.</def>
<mark>[Slang, U. S.]</mark><--shill?-->⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>An instrument for applying a percussion cap to a gun
or cartridge.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Capping plane</ent>⟦br⟧
